And a National Security Council
spokesman
said that the U.S. would review
its support

28:42.154 --> 28:44.156 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
of the Saudi-led coalition.

28:44.189 --> 28:49.628 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For more on the situation, I'm
joined by Michael
Hanna, a senior fellow at the
Century Foundation.

28:49.661 --> 28:51.463 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Welcome to you.

28:51.496 --> 28:54.933 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There was already so much
concern and anger
over civilian casualties and
deaths in this

28:54.967 --> 28:55.934 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
conflict.

28:55.968 --> 28:57.869 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
How important is this new
incident?

28:57.903 --> 28:59.972 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MICHAEL HANNA, Senior Fellow,
Century Foundation:
Well, it's gotten a lot more
attention than

29:00.005 --> 29:01.873 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
this war usually does.

29:01.907 --> 29:09.615 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think that's partly
because of the nature
of this attack and the scope of
the damage.

29:09.648 --> 29:11.450 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
This was a really horrific
attack.

29:11.483 --> 29:21.059 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It happened on a funeral hall
with a huge
number of senior Yemeni figures,
tribal figures

29:21.093 --> 29:23.729 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and political leaders.

29:23.762 --> 29:29.434 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And it does seem like a
difference in time,
like a red line had been crossed
in bombing

29:29.468 --> 29:32.971 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
this kind of funeral gathering.

29:33.005 --> 29:37.342 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And for that reason, it's gotten
a lot of
attention and a lot of negative
attention.

29:37.376 --> 29:40.812 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the reaction of the United
States has
been different.

29:40.846 --> 29:45.817 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have seen horrific bombings
in the past,
but this has elicited a
different kind of

29:45.851 --> 29:47.619 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
response from the United States.

29:47.653 --> 29:51.390 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Before we get to
that, just
remind us briefly where things
stand in this

29:51.423 --> 29:52.557 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
conflict in Yemen.

29:52.591 --> 29:55.394 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And what's behind the Saudi-led
bombing?

29:55.427 --> 30:01.933 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MICHAEL HANNA: Well, the Saudi
military campaign
began in March of 2015, so it's
been going

30:01.967 --> 30:03.835 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
on about a year-and-a-half.

30:03.869 --> 30:09.107 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, of course, Yemen and Saudi
are border
countries, so Saudi has looked
at Yemen differently

30:09.141 --> 30:14.179 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
than it does at other conflicts,
say, Syria,
for example.

30:14.212 --> 30:20.352 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That being said, it is quite
different to
see Saudi Arabia engaged in
direct military

30:20.385 --> 30:21.620 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
conflict.

30:21.653 --> 30:25.057 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They began a military campaign
about a year-and-a-half
ago.

30:25.090 --> 30:26.758 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They were joined by other Gulf
states.

30:26.792 --> 30:31.663 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, of course, they are getting
support from
the United States and the United
Kingdom.

30:31.697 --> 30:34.700 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And so this is a difference in
kind.

30:34.733 --> 30:39.037 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I think Saudi Arabia sees the
region changing.

30:39.071 --> 30:41.940 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's quite concerned about the
influence of
Iran.

30:41.973 --> 30:48.480 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It sees in the Houthis, the
rebel movement
that essentially overthrew the
government

30:48.513 --> 30:53.985 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in Yemen, as a kind of extension
of Iranian
influence, as a proxy force.

30:54.019 --> 30:58.657 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And while the United States has
a differing
view of the conflict, doesn't
necessarily

30:58.690 --> 31:06.031 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
agree about the Saudi analysis
of the conflict,
it has clearly reached a point
for Saudi Arabia

31:06.064 --> 31:10.535 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in its own calculations that
enough is enough.

31:10.569 --> 31:16.708 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And some of this is about
establishing deterrent
capacity and trying to change
the kind of

31:16.742 --> 31:18.844 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
regional balance of power at the
moment.

31:18.877 --> 31:22.814 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Well, so, to the
extent the
U.S. has supported this Saudi
effort, and

31:22.848 --> 31:27.886 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
yet there have been many
strains, particularly
over casualties among civilians.

31:27.919 --> 31:29.154 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
What now?

31:29.187 --> 31:32.257 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When they talk about a review,
what do you
see happening?

31:32.290 --> 31:35.260 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MICHAEL HANNA: Well, I think
it's high time
that there is a review.

31:35.293 --> 31:41.133 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The statement by the NSC this
weekend suggested
that U.S. security operation is
not a blank

31:41.166 --> 31:42.901 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
check.

31:42.934 --> 31:47.172 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think, for a long time
now, the United
States has hoped that the Saudis
and others

31:47.205 --> 31:52.778 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
would essentially declare
victory and focus
on a political settlement.

31:52.811 --> 31:55.414 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I think that's still the
American position.

31:55.447 --> 31:58.650 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And that has been voiced
publicly and privately.

31:58.683 --> 32:03.989 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I do think this seems
different, that
the United States, because of
this latest

32:04.022 --> 32:10.529 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
incident, is going to be much
more keen in
bringing about a cessation of
hostilities,

32:10.562 --> 32:17.135 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and much more keen on focusing
on the diplomatic
track, which has sputtered on
through various

32:17.169 --> 32:21.773 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
iterations, but has failed to
have any kind
of lasting impact.

32:21.807 --> 32:26.812 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I think the United States
has a very different
view about the utility -- the
continuing utility

32:26.845 --> 32:32.250 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of this military campaign and
the prospects
for it to be particularly
successful in the

32:32.284 --> 32:33.585 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
coming months.

32:33.618 --> 32:36.154 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: All right,
Michael Hanna, thank
you very much.

32:36.188 --> 32:42.160 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MICHAEL HANNA: Thank you.

32:42.194 --> 32:53.238 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Earlier in the
program,
we told you about the
record-breaking flooding

32:53.271 --> 32:55.073 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in North Carolina.

32:55.106 --> 33:00.212 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Hurricane Matthew also left a
wake of damage
on its way to North Carolina
along the coasts

33:00.245 --> 33:01.947 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of three states.

33:01.980 --> 33:06.585 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Billed as the oldest city in
America, St.
Augustine, Florida, was one of
the places

33:06.618 --> 33:08.420 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
that felt the storm's might.

33:08.453 --> 33:13.859 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The small coastal town of nearly
14,000, which
dates back to the 16th century,
is only now

33:13.892 --> 33:16.361 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
emerging from this weekend's
storm.

33:16.394 --> 33:19.364 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I was there yesterday.

33:19.397 --> 33:24.269 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It looked like one big garage
sale on Solana
Road in St. Augustine, Florida.

33:24.302 --> 33:30.842 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But everything in the front
yards was contaminated,
couches, mattresses, family
keepsakes all

33:30.876 --> 33:34.212 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
soaked by the floods after
Hurricane Matthew.

33:34.246 --> 33:38.250 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Families were racing to get it
all out before
the moisture turned to mold and
made its way

33:38.283 --> 33:40.085 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
into the walls.

33:40.118 --> 33:41.953 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NANCY SHAVER, Mayor of St.
Augustine, Florida:
When you evacuate, you take only
the things

33:41.987 --> 33:43.889 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
that you really find
irreplaceable.

33:43.922 --> 33:50.228 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But this is the whole -- these
are all the
things that may be replaceable,
but they're

33:50.262 --> 33:52.297 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
what give you something to come
home to.

33:52.330 --> 33:55.934 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Mayor Nancy
Shaver took
us to one of the low-lying areas
that was

33:55.967 --> 33:57.702 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
hardest-hit.

33:57.736 --> 34:02.841 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The sewer pumps were still
offline, meaning
underground waste was
overflowing onto the

34:02.874 --> 34:04.009 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
street.

34:04.042 --> 34:06.645 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Residents were only allowed back
into the
area Saturday.

34:06.678 --> 34:11.917 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NANCY SHAVER: Your home is where
you're supposed
to go to be peaceful, restful,
be with your

34:11.950 --> 34:13.285 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
family, sleep, eat.

34:13.318 --> 34:15.420 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And none of these things are
possible in these
homes.

34:15.453 --> 34:19.190 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: One of the
homeowners on
this block, the city manager,
John Regan.

34:19.224 --> 34:20.558 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
What did you have to throw out?

34:20.592 --> 34:21.493 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN REGAN, City Manager, St.
Augustine, Florida:
Everything.

34:21.526 --> 34:22.460 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: How many feet
of water?

34:22.494 --> 34:24.362 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JOHN REGAN: My house was two
feet of water.

34:24.396 --> 34:28.533 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Tasked with
coordinating
the city's recovery effort, now
working furiously

34:28.566 --> 34:29.834 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
on his own.

34:29.868 --> 34:32.737 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN REGAN: And these houses are
at this level
of destruction.

34:32.771 --> 34:36.675 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: While trying
to salvage
what he could from his home, he
was also trying

34:36.708 --> 34:41.379 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to prevent more fires like the
ones the city
has been fighting every night
since the storm.

34:41.413 --> 34:44.950 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN REGAN: So, and all these
houses that
have been flooded, when we bring
the power

34:44.983 --> 34:47.986 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
back, you got to be sensitive
that there's
no short-circuiting.

34:48.019 --> 34:52.490 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Regan is
luckier than some
just up the coast, who will
never move back

34:52.524 --> 34:54.292 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
into their homes again.

34:54.326 --> 34:58.396 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The storm's waves gouged deep
beneath the
foundations of some homes, and
surge-driven

34:58.430 --> 35:02.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
waters lifted and washed away
everything they
could.

35:02.167 --> 35:06.004 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The debris is not limited to the
coastline,
but inlets as well.

35:06.037 --> 35:11.376 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Marinas usually full of tourists
and boaters
are shut down because floating
junk is a danger

35:11.409 --> 35:14.546 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to boats and several docks have
lost their
moorings.

35:14.579 --> 35:18.550 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BILL HUNSICKER, Charter Boat
Captain: We're
ready to go fishing, but, at
this point, this

35:18.583 --> 35:20.819 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
marina, we can't get our boats
back in here.

35:20.852 --> 35:23.955 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Bill Hunsicker
captains
a charter boat for sport
fishermen.

35:23.989 --> 35:30.462 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He says he can last two weeks
without customers
before he has to make tough
decisions.

35:30.495 --> 35:35.200 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In the city's historic Old Town,
most businesses
remained shuttered, as they
dried out and

35:35.233 --> 35:36.301 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
cleaned up.

35:36.334 --> 35:39.104 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOMAN: This is the oldest bar in
the oldest
city.

35:39.137 --> 35:43.441 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: The local
watering hole
that rarely closes stopped for
Matthew.

35:43.475 --> 35:47.078 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOMAN: Usually, we have a
hurricane party,
but, this year, we didn't have
any power.

35:47.112 --> 35:48.079 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
So...

35:48.113 --> 35:49.080 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOMAN: And it was a really bad
one.

35:49.114 --> 35:50.482 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Nobody wanted to be here.

35:50.515 --> 35:52.417 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JORGE RIVERA, Blogger: So, this
is where the
bulk of the water came.

35:52.450 --> 35:56.254 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Blogger Jorge
Rivera wanted
to stay and track the storm.

35:56.287 --> 35:59.057 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JORGE RIVERA: The water's up to
my waist.

35:59.090 --> 36:03.228 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: He captured
some of the
earliest scenes of Matthew's
arrival.

36:03.261 --> 36:05.497 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Over the weekend, he continued
to document
its toll.

36:05.530 --> 36:11.503 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JORGE RIVERA: This was scary,
because it's
not so much that the hurricane
is powerful.

36:11.536 --> 36:14.439 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's that you're in such a
vulnerable place.

36:14.472 --> 36:16.741 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Now he wonders
whether it
would have been worth it.

36:16.775 --> 36:21.513 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JORGE RIVERA: The question is,
once they find
your body, they say, was he a
fool or was

36:21.546 --> 36:22.514 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
he brave?

36:22.547 --> 36:23.515 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
So, I don't know.

36:23.548 --> 36:24.516 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I don't have an answer for that.

36:24.549 --> 36:26.451 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: But Rivera
wasn't alone.

36:26.484 --> 36:31.022 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Mayor Shaver says almost half
the city stayed
behind, many who didn't have the
means to

36:31.056 --> 36:36.361 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
evacuate and others who were
homeless and
out of reach, numbers she hopes
to change

36:36.394 --> 36:37.662 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in the future.

36:37.695 --> 36:40.198 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
How do you build in resilience
to face something
like this?

36:40.231 --> 36:44.069 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NANCY SHAVER: Well, this is a --
we have had
450 years of practice.

36:44.102 --> 36:46.638 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We are an extraordinarily
resilient city.

36:46.671 --> 36:48.173 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's a real community.

36:48.206 --> 36:51.910 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It has a very rich fabric of
reaching out,
connecting and helping folks.

36:51.943 --> 36:55.947 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: That sentiment
moved the
owners of Le Macaron to hand out
sweets to

36:55.980 --> 36:57.882 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
their local firefighters.

36:57.916 --> 37:01.019 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Recent transplants from France,
they're overwhelmed
by the support

37:01.052 --> 37:08.193 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STEPHANE JUSKOWIAK, Le Macaron:
Here, we see
this, and it's -- we don't have
this in Europe,

37:08.226 --> 37:09.394 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in France.

37:09.427 --> 37:13.264 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I'm sorry to say that, but,
here, it's very
different.

37:13.298 --> 37:19.104 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And we -- there was lots of
people coming
every 15 minutes, saying, hey,
we can help

37:19.137 --> 37:20.905 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
us.

37:20.939 --> 37:25.009 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: This city has
soldiered
on through challenges for more
than 400 years.

37:25.043 --> 37:29.814 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
City hall, which was flooded,
reopened to
essential personnel today.

