1992 to a school to train
students from developing
countries grappling with climate
change and

38:32.143 --> 38:34.045 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
growing populations.

38:34.078 --> 38:38.950 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Funds came from the U.S. and
Costa Rican governments
and the Michigan-based Kellogg
Foundation.

38:38.983 --> 38:42.620 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOSE ZAGLUL, Co-Founder, EARTH
University:
When we first came to this
property, the whole

38:42.654 --> 38:48.493 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
river was contaminated with the
blue plastic
bag that also have chemical
inside to protect

38:48.526 --> 38:50.562 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
it, to protect it from insects.

38:50.595 --> 38:56.601 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And when the first group of
students came,
we brought them here and we
started to pick

38:56.634 --> 38:58.469 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
all the plastic.

38:58.503 --> 39:03.074 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Today,
university co-founder
Jose Zaglul says the blue
plastic bags are

39:03.107 --> 39:09.647 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
recycled and tons of plant
waste, stalks,
fruit that don't make the grade.

39:09.681 --> 39:13.084 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Things that used to be discarded
are collected
and fed to livestock.

39:13.117 --> 39:17.422 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOSE ZAGLUL: Now we don't use
chemicals in
the bags.

39:17.455 --> 39:20.892 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And we also are using an organic
fungicide.

39:20.925 --> 39:27.999 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: These
bananas are labeled
as responsibly grown and sold
across the U.S.

39:28.032 --> 39:29.901 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in Whole Foods stores.

39:29.934 --> 39:33.171 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The enterprise supports dozens
of local jobs
and scholarships.

39:33.204 --> 39:36.407 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOSE ZAGLUL: That girl over
there, she's from
Panama.

39:36.441 --> 39:38.876 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
This guy is from Brazil.

39:38.910 --> 39:42.914 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I think she is from Ecuador.

39:42.947 --> 39:45.617 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That guy you see, he's from
Somaliland in
Africa.

39:45.650 --> 39:48.786 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Forty-three
countries
are represented here.

39:48.820 --> 39:53.091 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A majority of the 400 students
depend on financial
aid.

39:53.124 --> 39:57.829 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
From 1,600 applications, about
110 are admitted
each year.

39:57.862 --> 40:05.470 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOSE ZAGLUL: What we attempt to
discover there
is their interest to go back to
their countries,

40:05.503 --> 40:13.811 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
because we are about forming
leaders and individuals
that really overcome barriers.

40:13.845 --> 40:21.953 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Yves
Rusanganwa is a first-year
student from Rwanda born soon
after that country's

40:21.986 --> 40:23.755 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
genocide.

40:23.788 --> 40:27.492 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
YVES RUSANGANWA, EARTH
University: I grew
up hearing about hunger, hearing
about poverty,

40:27.525 --> 40:29.727 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
hearing epidemic diseases.

40:29.761 --> 40:31.562 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I grew up in that environment.

40:31.596 --> 40:37.869 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, as I was growing up, I grew
up a passion
inside of me of doing something
in this world

40:37.902 --> 40:39.671 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and try to change that history.

40:39.704 --> 40:43.941 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Many
students say a lack
of knowledge hinders
productivity and keeps

40:43.975 --> 40:47.879 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
most farmers in their homelands
in poverty.

40:47.912 --> 40:54.185 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Devotha Tumushimiyimana is also
from Rwanda,
a nation the size of Maryland
with a population

40:54.218 --> 40:55.720 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of 11 million.

40:55.753 --> 40:57.689 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DEVOTHA TUMUSHIMIYIMANA, EARTH
University:
My country is a small country.

40:57.722 --> 41:03.961 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, I would like also to teach
people how
they can use -- I mean, how they
can do agriculture

41:03.995 --> 41:05.763 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in small land.

41:05.797 --> 41:10.568 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Jose Zaglul
says doing
agriculture on small land, or
even no land,

41:10.601 --> 41:12.470 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
is an important part of the
curriculum.

41:12.503 --> 41:20.244 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOSE ZAGLUL: At home, in the
schools, in rooftops
in the cities, and you don't
have to utilize

41:20.278 --> 41:23.481 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
so much energy and fossil fuels
to transport
them.

41:23.514 --> 41:28.319 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Across
campus, fruits
and vegetables are grown in
unlikely containers,

41:28.353 --> 41:30.121 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
with unlikely tools.

41:30.154 --> 41:34.425 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOSE ZAGLUL: All the bottles,
you can fill
them with water, with -- and
then it's like

41:34.459 --> 41:36.260 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
drip irrigation.

41:36.294 --> 41:40.098 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: The campus
tries to model
the ideal carbon-neutral world
it wants its

41:40.131 --> 41:41.933 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
graduates to help create.

41:41.966 --> 41:47.438 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Zaglul says that's sometimes
involved taking
risks, like the decision at the
start to keep

41:47.472 --> 41:49.307 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
producing bananas.

41:49.340 --> 41:55.046 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOSE ZAGLUL: It used to cost us
25 cents more
per box to do all the
sustainable practices.

41:55.079 --> 41:58.416 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And nobody would pay us for
that.

41:58.449 --> 42:04.922 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I tell you, we were losing
money, but we had
to show the students that it is
possible to

42:04.956 --> 42:06.758 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
do sustainable business.

42:06.791 --> 42:11.396 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Possible, he
says, because,
over time, recycling and not
using pesticides

42:11.429 --> 42:13.164 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
save money.

42:13.197 --> 42:17.535 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Then came the right large
customer, Whole
Foods.

42:17.568 --> 42:24.242 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Besides the classroom and field
emphasis on
sustainable practices, students
are encouraged

42:24.275 --> 42:26.611 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to develop business ideas.

42:26.644 --> 42:31.949 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Twenty-three-year-old Diderot
Saintilma has
plans for when he returns to his
native Haiti.

42:31.983 --> 42:35.753 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
DIDEROT SAINTILMA, EARTH
University (through
translator): Where I come from,
there are

42:35.787 --> 42:37.321 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
a lot of peanut farmers.

42:37.355 --> 42:40.324 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
They don't do very much
post-harvest processing.

42:40.358 --> 42:45.163 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So I would like to start an
association or
cooperative of small peanut
farmers, so they

42:45.196 --> 42:46.864 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
can get added value for
products.

42:46.898 --> 42:51.769 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Many
graduates have taken
ideas from here to the business
world.

42:51.803 --> 42:55.907 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For Costa Rican Joaquin Viquez,
it was animal
waste recycling.

42:55.940 --> 43:01.779 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Solids are separated to make
fertilizer, while
large bladders or bio-digesters
break down

43:01.813 --> 43:04.749 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
liquid wastes to capture
methane, or biogas.

43:04.782 --> 43:07.752 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOAQUIN VIQUEZ, EARTH University
Graduate:
This is like five times thinner
than what

43:07.785 --> 43:08.886 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
we use now.

43:08.920 --> 43:11.122 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Its not new
technology,
he says.

43:11.155 --> 43:14.091 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It simply wasn't commercialized
for farms
in developing countries.

43:14.125 --> 43:17.995 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOAQUIN VIQUEZ: There was no one
you could
call or no store you could go
and say, hey,

43:18.029 --> 43:19.864 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I want a digester.

43:19.897 --> 43:25.603 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so we made it technically
accessible and
we do a lot of efforts to make
it economically

43:25.636 --> 43:27.738 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
feasible for a farmer.

43:27.772 --> 43:34.745 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: On this day,
they were
installing a digester at the
Calderon family

43:34.779 --> 43:37.682 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
farm, about 100 head of dairy
and beef cows.

43:37.715 --> 43:42.720 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARIA AGUILLAR CALDERON, Farmer
(through translator):
I took a course recently at the
National Institute

43:42.753 --> 43:46.357 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of Learning, and they talked
about global
warming and hygiene.

43:46.390 --> 43:49.427 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I really came back wanting
to have a clean
farm.

43:49.460 --> 43:56.067 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, I contacted a microfinance
agency, talked
to my husband and used our
savings to do this.

43:56.100 --> 44:01.072 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Viquez says
not only will
this family be reducing
greenhouse gases emitted

44:01.105 --> 44:06.511 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
by unprocessed animal wastes,
but their energy
savings over time will more than
cover the

44:06.544 --> 44:08.446 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
digester's $3,400 cost.

44:08.479 --> 44:13.851 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOAQUIN VIQUEZ: They're not
going to have
to use any firewood or propane
for the cooking.

44:13.885 --> 44:15.453 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I know they're going to have
surplus.

44:15.486 --> 44:20.057 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Viquez is
one of about
2,000 EARTH University alumni.

44:20.091 --> 44:25.796 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Jose Zaglul says each on average
has created
four other jobs, and their
influence has spread

44:25.830 --> 44:27.565 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in other ways.

44:27.598 --> 44:32.837 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Many commercial banana
producers, he says,
have adopted practices that
began here.

44:32.870 --> 44:38.142 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," this is
Fred de Sam
Lazaro in Guapiles, Costa Rica.

44:38.175 --> 44:43.114 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Fred's
reporting is a partnership
with the Under-Told Stories
Project at the

44:43.147 --> 44:48.619 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
University of St. Thomas in
Minnesota.

44:48.653 --> 45:00.097 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Ruth Bader Ginsburg broke
countless barriers
for women in the legal
profession long before

45:00.131 --> 45:04.368 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
she was tapped by President Bill
Clinton for
the highest court in the land.

45:04.402 --> 45:08.806 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Now she has published a
collection of her
writings and speeches called "My
Own Words."

45:08.839 --> 45:12.510 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For this latest addition to the
"NewsHour"
Bookshelf, Gwen Ifill sat down
with Justice

45:12.543 --> 45:14.779 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Ginsburg recently at the Supreme
Court.

45:14.812 --> 45:18.015 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Justice Ginsburg,
thank you for
speaking with us.

45:18.049 --> 45:22.420 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I want to start by -- with a
broader question
than you even address in your
book, which

45:22.453 --> 45:25.489 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is, you have become something of
a folk hero
to some women.

45:25.523 --> 45:27.191 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Did you see that coming?

45:27.224 --> 45:30.127 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RUTH BADER GINSBURG, Associate
Justice, U.S.
Supreme Court: It is utterly
amazing.

45:30.161 --> 45:32.763 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Of course I didn't see it
coming.

45:32.797 --> 45:39.370 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it was all the creation of a
second-year
student, second-year law
student, at NYU.

45:39.403 --> 45:41.505 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It came about this way.

45:41.539 --> 45:49.780 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She was reading a court's
decision that invalidated
a very significant part of the
Voting Rights

45:49.814 --> 45:50.881 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Act of 1965.

45:50.915 --> 45:53.684 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And she was angry.

45:53.718 --> 45:57.822 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And then she remembered that I
had said anger
is a useless emotion.

45:57.855 --> 45:59.590 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It doesn't get you any place.

45:59.624 --> 46:01.292 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Do something positive.

46:01.325 --> 46:08.232 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, she created this tumbler
starting with
my dissent, and then it took off
into the

46:08.265 --> 46:09.967 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
wild blue yonder.

46:10.001 --> 46:13.904 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: You know, some
people would say
it's about politics, but I
wonder if it's

46:13.938 --> 46:19.910 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
not also about your presence,
your very existence
on the court and the way that
you write and

46:19.944 --> 46:23.047 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the way that you sometimes take
on your colleagues.

46:23.080 --> 46:28.452 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RUTH BADER GINSBURG: I would
like to think
so, but I certainly was given a
tremendous

46:28.486 --> 46:33.658 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
boost into the public arena by
the Notorious
R.B.G.

46:33.691 --> 46:42.099 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
When I was asked about it, I
said, well, it's
exactly right, because Notorious
B.I.G. and

46:42.133 --> 46:45.803 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I had something in common?

46:45.836 --> 46:46.871 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
You did?

46:46.904 --> 46:48.039 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
What?

46:48.072 --> 46:50.808 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We were both born and bred in
Brooklyn, New
York.

46:50.841 --> 46:51.809 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

46:51.842 --> 46:54.211 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: You ever consider
being a rapper?

46:54.245 --> 46:55.413 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

46:55.446 --> 46:58.215 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RUTH BADER GINSBURG: I don't
think I have
that talent.

46:58.249 --> 46:59.784 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Well, neither do I.

46:59.817 --> 47:03.220 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I want to talk to you about
someone you give
a lot of credit to in this book.

47:03.254 --> 47:05.022 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And that is your late husband,
Marty Ginsburg.

47:05.056 --> 47:08.592 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And one of the things that
someone said is
that you would never have been
on the court

47:08.626 --> 47:09.593 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
without him.

47:09.627 --> 47:10.594 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Do you agree with that?

47:10.628 --> 47:12.830 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
RUTH BADER GINSBURG: It's
absolutely true.

47:12.863 --> 47:20.271 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
One of my law clerks at the
Court of Appeals
said at the time that Clinton
was considering

47:20.304 --> 47:27.144 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
who would be his first nominee
to the court,
he said, "You will be on the
list, but you

47:27.178 --> 47:33.184 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
will be probably be around
number 25, unless
you do something to promote
yourself."

47:33.217 --> 47:39.123 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
So, I'm not very good at
promotion, but Marty
was.

47:39.156 --> 47:46.964 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And he was tireless in his
effort to see that
I would be the nominee.

47:46.997 --> 47:52.303 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Just the way you
write about,
speak about Marty, it's almost
like a present

47:52.336 --> 47:54.171 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
tense presence in your life.

47:54.205 --> 47:58.242 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RUTH BADER GINSBURG: He will be
present in
my life as long as I live.

47:58.275 --> 48:02.246 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I have his portrait in my
bedroom.

48:02.279 --> 48:05.850 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I look at it and say, "You
would probably
like what I am doing now."

48:05.883 --> 48:07.651 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

48:07.685 --> 48:12.189 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Out of all the
speeches and the
writings that you have collected
in this book,

48:12.223 --> 48:14.592 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
what do you get the most
frequent questions
about?

48:14.625 --> 48:17.928 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
What do young people, older
people ask you?

48:17.962 --> 48:26.670 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
RUTH BADER GINSBURG: One
question is, did
you always want to be a judge,
or, more exorbitantly,

48:26.704 --> 48:29.306 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
did you always want to be a
Supreme Court
justice?

48:29.340 --> 48:36.113 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I try to explain the way things
were in the
not-so-good-old-days.

48:36.147 --> 48:45.089 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, when I graduated from law
school in 1959,
there wasn't a single woman on
any federal

48:45.122 --> 48:46.824 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
bench.

48:46.857 --> 48:54.799 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It wouldn't be a realistic
ambition for a
woman to want to become a
federal judge.

48:54.832 --> 49:00.905 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It wasn't realistic until Jimmy
Carter became
our president.

49:00.938 --> 49:07.344 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He looked around at the federal
judiciary
and said: That's nice, but they
all look like

49:07.378 --> 49:09.113 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
me.

49:09.146 --> 49:16.220 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, I am determined to appoint
members of
minority groups and women in
numbers to the

49:16.253 --> 49:23.594 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
federal bench, so we will use
the talent of
all of the people of the United
States, and

49:23.627 --> 49:25.629 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
not just some of them.

49:25.663 --> 49:31.802 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
GWEN IFILL: I'm not sure
everyone knows how
extensive your interest in
women's issues,

49:31.836 --> 49:35.105 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
women's rights were long before
you got to
the court.

49:35.139 --> 49:38.242 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Is that something which this can
also begin
to illuminate?

49:38.275 --> 49:40.211 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
RUTH BADER GINSBURG: Yes.

49:40.244 --> 49:45.382 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The book includes one of my many
speeches
about why we need an equal
rights amendment.

49:45.416 --> 49:51.255 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Do you feel that --
as a liberal,
that conservative women, men can
identify

49:51.288 --> 49:53.023 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
with you as well?

49:53.057 --> 49:58.028 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RUTH BADER GINSBURG: The label
liberal or
conservative, any -- every time
I hear that,

49:58.062 --> 50:03.701 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think of the great Gilbert and
Sullivan
song from "Iolanthe."

50:03.734 --> 50:13.377 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It goes, every gal and every boy
that's born
alive is either a little liberal
or else a

50:13.410 --> 50:15.779 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
little conservative.

50:15.813 --> 50:17.581 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
What do those labels mean?

50:17.615 --> 50:20.317 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It depends on whose ox is being
gored.

50:20.351 --> 50:24.722 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: You got into a
little trouble
for making a comment about
Donald Trump this

50:24.755 --> 50:25.723 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
year.

50:25.756 --> 50:27.424 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Do you still regret it?

50:27.458 --> 50:34.365 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RUTH BADER GINSBURG: I said what
I had to
say about that, and I will not
address that

50:34.398 --> 50:35.366 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
subject again.

50:35.399 --> 50:36.734 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
GWEN IFILL: That's fair.

50:36.767 --> 50:39.203 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Let me ask you another question
about what's
happening right now.

50:39.236 --> 50:40.471 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Do you know Merrick Garland?

50:40.504 --> 50:44.275 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RUTH BADER GINSBURG: Yes, I know
Merrick quite,
quite well.

50:44.308 --> 50:49.480 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He is now the chief judge of the
court on
which I served for many years.

50:49.513 --> 50:51.916 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And he's an expert in
administrative law.

50:51.949 --> 50:55.152 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So, I have read his writings.

50:55.185 --> 51:03.294 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I wish that the spirit that
prevailed in 1993,
when I was nominated, I wish
that that could

51:03.327 --> 51:04.695 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
be restored.

51:04.728 --> 51:12.069 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
In 1993, the vote on me was 96
to 3.

51:12.102 --> 51:16.440 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I was nominated on June 14.

51:16.473 --> 51:19.310 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I was confirmed on August 3.

51:19.343 --> 51:21.045 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: It's very different
now.

51:21.078 --> 51:22.112 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
RUTH BADER GINSBURG: Yes.

51:22.146 --> 51:26.717 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But there was a true bipartisan
spirit prevailing.

51:26.750 --> 51:29.720 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Democrat and Republicans worked
together,
and they got things done.

51:29.753 --> 51:33.223 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Everybody wonders
whether you're
going to be ever done.

51:33.257 --> 51:35.426 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You have moved the bar many
different times.

51:35.459 --> 51:36.794 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
RUTH BADER GINSBURG: Yes.

51:36.827 --> 51:40.464 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
At first, I said I wanted to
stay as long
as Justice Brandeis did.

51:40.497 --> 51:44.234 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He was appointed at the same age
I was, 60.

51:44.268 --> 51:48.539 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But he retired when he was 83,
which I am.

51:48.572 --> 51:54.044 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, my answer is, I will do this
job as long
as I can do it full-steam.

51:54.078 --> 51:59.817 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, at my age, that means you
take it year
by year, though I am confident
that, this

51:59.850 --> 52:05.255 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
